<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,679,1244]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,895,920]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[406,515,895,920]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1847,1870]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1823]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Belciades spp., imagines. 1, 2 – B. niveola (1 – Russian Far East, 2 – Korea); 3, 4 – B. koenigi, China (3 – holotype), 5, 6 – B. hoenei, China, (5 – holotype, 6 – paratype); 7, 8 – B. sugii (7 – Thailand, 8 – China)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203317/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">
Figs. 
<number box="[470,515,895,920]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" value="7.8">7, 8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[657,781,895,920]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="3.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" unit="mm" value="32.5" valueMax="34.0" valueMin="31.0">31–34 mm</quantity>
. The species is close to 
<emphasis box="[1053,1135,896,920]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicName box="[1053,1130,896,920]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">hoenei</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but differs in bluish-green tint in coloration of forewing, and details of wing pattern. In male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1007,1089,932,956]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1774,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1753]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1753]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Belciades spp., male genitalia. 17 – B. niveola, Russian Far East, genit. prep. 1641 ZFMK; 18 – B. koenigi, paratype, China, genit. prep. 1641 ZFMK; 19 – B. hoenei, paratype, genit. prep. 1639 ZFMK; 20 – B. sugii, Thailand, genit. prep. 7277 GB." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203319/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">
Fig. 
<number box="[1060,1089,932,956]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
) it differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1268,1343,932,956]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[1268,1343,932,956]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in more massive valva, which is not expanded distally, with obscure neck; in structure of juxta by bearing a sclerotised dentate ridge at middle, which is absent in 
<emphasis box="[614,698,1004,1028]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicName box="[614,691,1004,1028]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">hoenei</taxonomicName>
;
</emphasis>
more massive distal extension of sacculus and more developed harpe. Shape of vesica is very similar to that 
<emphasis box="[656,766,1040,1064]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">
of 
<taxonomicName box="[685,762,1040,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">hoenei</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but differs in having more numerous spinulate cornuti with wide base and an isolated one moved to apical part of vesica. Female is much smaller in size than that of 
<emphasis box="[1324,1406,1076,1100]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicName box="[1324,1402,1076,1100]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">hoenei</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
In female genitalia it differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[498,573,1112,1136]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[498,573,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by twice larger papillae anales, horseshoe-shaped antevaginal plate, which in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,226,1148,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[151,226,1148,1172]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented by paired triangular plates, and larger corpus bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="43" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,679,1244]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,498,1183,1208]" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Distribution and biology.</emphasis>
The species is distributed in mountain regions of North 
<collectingCountry box="[1144,1246,1184,1208]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1259,1313,1185,1208]" name="Laos" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">Laos</collectingCountry>
and South 
<collectingCountry box="[151,222,1220,1244]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="43">China</collectingCountry>
. The label data indicate that it has at least two generations, flying in April and September.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
